transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: I got a billing from you guys, like a recurring billing.

Speaker 2: I bought some of your products about a month or so ago,

Speaker 1: and I just got billed again for your product again.

Speaker 2: I never signed up for a recurring billing.

Speaker 1: Yeah, did you get an opportunity to read the terms

Speaker 2: and conditions after placing your first order?

Speaker 1: When I did the order, it said that you take it and I get it,

Speaker 2: and that was it.

Speaker 1: I didn't know.

Speaker 2: It doesn't state that anywhere on your website, sir,

Speaker 1: but I was asking you, did you read the terms and conditions

Speaker 2: after placing your first order?

Speaker 1: No, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay, no worries.

Speaker 1: So basically it just tells you how every order is a prescription-based

Speaker 2: order because these are real medications through Pfizer,

Speaker 1: and they need to have a refill date to be activated.

Speaker 2: So the doctor chooses your frequency, but you can call us to modify it,

Speaker 1: and it just looks like you didn't modify it.

Speaker 2: Can I get your last name and a zip code so I can pull up your account?

Speaker 1: I didn't modify anything.

Speaker 2: My name is Walter Bell.

Speaker 1: My zip code is 85233.

Speaker 2: I got the transaction ID number that you guys sent to PayPal, too.

Speaker 1: Oh, yeah, and I have your account pulled up here.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you didn't modify it,

Speaker 1: so that means you didn't change it from the original date the doctor set

Speaker 2: for you, which is two months.

Speaker 1: That's how your receipts were billed today.

Speaker 2: I see that the order is currently at the pharmacy,

Speaker 1: so I can cancel it out for you and help you with the refund.

Speaker 2: Cancel it out for me, sir.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no problem.

Speaker 1: It will take three to five business days to hit your account.

Speaker 2: However, regarding the prescription,

Speaker 1: it needs to have a refill date to stay active.

Speaker 2: It doesn't mean you need to take the package

Speaker 1: or get the order processed, but it needs a refill date.

Speaker 2: What I could do for you, though,

Speaker 1: is set you up for every six-month freeze plan.

Speaker 2: That way you can retain access to this for when you need it down the road.

Speaker 1: Every six months?

Speaker 2: Well, yeah, you don't need to get it every six months,

Speaker 1: but that's the furthest we can take it.

Speaker 2: That way you can call us and let us know, hey, I need it before then,

Speaker 1: and say, hey, you know what, push it even further.

Speaker 2: We have no problem with that whatsoever.

Speaker 1: Well, why don't we just hold off on that for right now,

Speaker 2: and I would appreciate that.

Speaker 1: Let's just cancel what we've got going here.

Speaker 2: If I need it, I will call you guys back again.

Speaker 1: Yeah, exactly.

Speaker 2: That's why I was mentioning the six-month plan, sir.

Speaker 1: That's the only method of doing that, because I'll cancel it out

Speaker 2: and give you the refund for that.

Speaker 1: It's not a problem.

Speaker 2: But for the refill date so the prescription remains active,

Speaker 1: I do need to set a refill date, which is why I was mentioning the six months.

Speaker 2: But you can always call us to push it even further if you need more time.

Speaker 1: Well, I don't want a refill right now, please.

Speaker 2: No, no, you won't get a refill right now.

Speaker 1: I already told you that you wouldn't.

Speaker 2: You're going to get a refill.

Speaker 1: You're talking about a refill.

Speaker 2: I'll get one in six months.

Speaker 1: Your prescription needs to – no, I didn't say that.

Speaker 2: I told you it needs a refill date to stay active.

Speaker 1: Without that, the prescription itself closes and the doctor shuts down the visit

Speaker 2: and you wouldn't be able to order in the future.

Speaker 1: However, if we just freeze it out for you like that,

Speaker 2: you're able to just call us and tell us, hey, I need six more months,

Speaker 1: or, hey, I just need you to send it out because I need them now.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Got it.

Speaker 1: So I'll just switch you over to that plan so you can retain access to your medication.

Speaker 2: You're all set.

Speaker 1: I made that modification to the six-month plan

Speaker 2: and I canceled out the order in the pharmacy.

Speaker 1: You'll get that refund back in three to five business days.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no problem.

Speaker 2: Have a good one.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
